## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 6 |
| **High** | 1 |
| **Medium** | 2 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is invoked, achieving ~95% line coverage, but almost nothing is actually *verified*. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken (returning wrong values, corrupting data, ignoring inputs).

---

### 🔴 Critical — Tests Giving False Confidence

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic — entire class)

The class methodically calls every public method with zero or trivial assertions. 6 of 10 tests have **no assertion at all**; 4 use only `Assert.IsNotNull` which merely checks a non-null reference was returned — not that it's *correct*.

---

#### 2. No Assertions — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)

```csharp
// BEFORE — proves nothing
_catalog.AddProduct(product);

// AFTER — verify the product is retrievable with correct data
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
```

#### 3. No Assertions — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 31)

```csharp
// BEFORE — never checks the price changed
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// AFTER
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
```

#### 4. No Assertions — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 38)

```csharp
// BEFORE — never confirms deletion
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

// AFTER
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

#### 5. No Assertions — `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)

```csharp
// BEFORE — discards the result entirely
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();

// AFTER
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();
Assert.AreEqual(1, count);
```

#### 6. No Assertions — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68)

```csharp
// BEFORE — never checks prices changed
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

// AFTER
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")?.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")?.Price);
```

#### 7. No Assertions — `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85)

